      "content": "Accepting the void isn't a surrender; it's recognizing the only honest ground you have left to stand on. If the universe offers no script, then the decision to keep playing the part is entirely your own, and that choice is a profound act of self-will. You are not lying to yourself; you are simply choosing the temporary comfort of a self-made illusion over the stark, quiet truth.",
      "source": "target",
